// Copy this file to Plaid.xcconfig (gitignored) and fill in real values from
// your Plaid dashboard (https://dashboard.plaid.com/team-settings/keys).
//
// PLAID_SANDBOX_SECRET is the Sandbox environment's secret only — this story
// (reservoir-adq.6.1) is Sandbox-only. Production switching is a separate
// story (reservoir-adq.6.2) and will introduce its own secret handling.
//
// PLAID_URL_SCHEME is the custom URL scheme LinkKit uses to reopen the app
// after an OAuth-institution redirect. Pick anything reasonably unique, e.g.
// your reverse-DNS bundle ID with a suffix — it must also be registered with
// Plaid as an "Allowed redirect URI" in the dashboard as
// `<scheme>://oauth`.
//
// These values are embedded into the built app's Info.plist and are
// readable by anyone with the .app bundle — acceptable only under this
// app's accepted risk posture (personal, sideloaded, single-user, not
// distributed). Do not commit Plaid.xcconfig.

PLAID_CLIENT_ID = your_plaid_client_id
PLAID_SANDBOX_SECRET = your_plaid_sandbox_secret
PLAID_URL_SCHEME = com.johnpease.reservoir.plaid
